.Dd March 10, 2001
.Dt ACL_CLEAR_PERMS 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm acl_clear_perms
.Nd clear permissions from a permission set
.Sh LIBRARY
.Lb libc
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In sys/types.h
.In sys/acl.h
.Ft int
.Fn acl_clear_perms "acl_permset_t permset_d"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Fn acl_clear_perms
function
is a POSIX.1e call that clears all permissions from permissions set
.Fa permset_d .
.Sh RETURN VALUES
.Rv -std acl_clear_perms
.Sh ERRORS
The
.Fn acl_clear_perms
function fails if:
.Bl -tag -width Er
.It Bq Er EINVAL
Argument
.Fa permset_d
is not a valid descriptor for a permission set.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr acl 3 ,
.Xr acl_add_perm 3 ,
.Xr acl_delete_perm 3 ,
.Xr acl_get_permset 3 ,
.Xr acl_set_permset 3 ,
.Xr posix1e 3
.Sh STANDARDS
POSIX.1e is described in IEEE POSIX.1e draft 17.
.Sh HISTORY
POSIX.1e support was introduced in
.Fx 4.0 .
The
.Fn acl_clear_perms
function was added in
.Fx 5.0 .
